# Test File Protection Rules

## 🚫 PROTECTED DIRECTORIES (DO NOT MODIFY)

The following directories contain test fixtures that define expected behavior:

- `tests/CodeLintTest/src/init_checker/src/` - Source test files
- `tests/CodeLintTest/src/init_checker/fixed/` - Expected output files
- `tests/CodeLintTest/build/` - Build artifacts

## ⚠️ AI ASSISTANTS - READ THIS FIRST

**These files are GOLDEN FILES. They define correctness.**

### NEVER:
- Modify files in protected directories
- "Fix" test files to make tests pass
- Change expected outputs
- Skip failing tests

### ALWAYS:
- Fix the CODE when tests fail
- Ask the user before updating baselines
- Document test changes in commit messages

### EXCEPTION:
You MAY:
- Add NEW test files (e.g., `tests/commands_test.cpp`)
- Modify test scripts (`tests/run_regression.sh`)
- Update test infrastructure (CMakeLists.txt)

## Enforcement

Pre-commit hook protects these files by:
- Running unit tests (GoogleTest)
- Running basic functionality checks
- Excluding protected directory tests

**REMEMBER**: Changing tests to pass = hiding bugs
